+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017cupowVWfCzFKjQvR92H6f","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have now thoroughly explored the entire codebase. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Complete Codebase Exploration Report\n\n### 1. Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── .git/                          (Git repository)\n├── .thunderdome/                  (Thunderdome test output)\n├── phases/                        (Phase requirement files)\n│   ├── phase-01.md\n│   ├── phase-02.md\n│   ├── phase-03.md\n│   ├── phase-04.md\n│   ├── phase-05.md\n│   ├── phase-06.md\n│   ├── phase-07.md\n│   ├── phase-08.md\n│   ├── phase-09.md\n│   ├── phase-10.md\n│   ├── phase-11.md\n│   └── phase-12.md\n├── src/                           (Source code - currently empty except .gitkeep)\n│   └── .gitkeep\n├── .eslintrc.cjs                 (ESLint configuration)\n├── .gitignore\n├── TASK.md                        (Main task description)\n├── package.json\n├── package-lock.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n└── vitest.config.ts\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. TASK.md (Main Requirements)\n\n**Project:** Build a fully-featured in-memory task queue system from scratch with 12 progressive phases.\n\n**Overview:**\n- System grows incrementally through 12 phases\n- Supports adding tasks, processing them, and managing their lifecycle\n- Similar to Bull, BeeQueue, or Celery but entirely in-memory with no external dependencies\n\n**12 Phases:**\n1. Basic queue - adding and processing tasks in order\n2. Named queues - multiple independent queues\n3. Priority - tasks with urgency levels\n4. Delayed tasks - tasks that wait before becoming available\n5. Retry with backoff - automatic retry when tasks fail\n6. Dead letter queue - permanent storage for repeatedly-failing tasks\n7. Task dependencies - tasks that wait for other tasks to finish\n8. Concurrency control - limiting how many tasks run at once\n9. Progress and cancellation - tracking and aborting work\n10. Recurring tasks - cron-like scheduled task creation\n11. Middleware - intercepting and transforming tasks in a pipeline\n12. Graceful shutdown - orderly wind-down of the system\n\n**Requirements:**\n- Export main API from `src/index.ts`\n- All implementation under `src/`\n- No external runtime dependencies (dev dependencies pre-installed)\n- Write tests to verify implementation\n- Must compile with TypeScript (`npm run build`)\n- Must pass linting (`npm run lint`)\n\n---\n\n### 3. All Phase Files (Complete Content)\n\n#### Phase 1: Basic FIFO Queue\n- Accept payload when adding task, return task object\n- Each task has unique ID (UUID), status, creation timestamp\n- Tasks start in \"pending\" state\n- Retrieving next task returns oldest pending task, transitions to \"processing\"\n- Return `null` if no tasks available\n- Way to check how many tasks are waiting\n\n#### Phase 2: Named Queues\n- Tasks added to specific named queue (or default if omitted)\n- Each queue operates independently\n- Retrieve task from specified queue only\n- Queue created implicitly when first task added\n- List all queue names\n- Non-existent/empty queue returns `null`\n- Backward-compatible with Phase 1\n\n#### Phase 3: Priority\n- Priority levels 1-10 (1=highest, default=5)\n- Retrieve higher-priority tasks (lower number) first\n- Same priority: FIFO order\n- Invalid priority values cause error\n- Priority per-queue\n- Task object exposes priority level\n\n#### Phase 4: Delayed and Scheduled Tasks\n- Task can have delay (milliseconds) or specific future availability time\n- Delayed tasks not returned until availability time passes\n- Non-delayed tasks preferred over unavailable delayed tasks\n- Multiple delayed tasks becoming available: ordered by availability time, then priority, then FIFO\n- Task object indicates availability time\n- Delays work with named queues\n\n#### Phase 5: Retry with Backoff\n- Mark processing task as completed or failed\n- Failed task with remaining retries: re-added with delay\n- Exponential backoff: `baseDelay * 2^(attempt - 1)` (e.g., 1s, 2s, 4s, ...)\n- Default max retries: 3 (configurable per task)\n- Base backoff delay: 1000ms (configurable per task)\n- Task tracks attempt count\n- Retried tasks keep original queue and priority\n- All retries exhausted: task remains in failed state\n\n#### Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue\n- Tasks with no retries left moved to DLQ of original queue\n- View all dead-lettered tasks for given queue\n- Dead-lettered tasks retain error information and failure count\n- Move dead-lettered task back to original queue for fresh retries\n- Clear all dead-lettered tasks for queue\n- Each named queue has own independent DLQ\n\n#### Phase 7: Task Dependencies\n- Specify list of task IDs that must complete before task becomes available\n- Task with unresolved dependencies is blocked, won't be returned\n- When dependency completes, check if blocked tasks are now unblocked\n- Detect and reject circular dependencies at task-creation time\n- Depending on non-existent task causes error\n- Failed dependency does NOT auto-fail dependents (remain blocked)\n- Way to inspect task's dependency status\n\n#### Phase 8: Concurrency Control\n- Each queue has maximum concurrency setting\n- Limits how many tasks in processing state simultaneously\n- If limit reached, retrieving task returns `null` even if pending tasks available\n- Completing/failing task frees up concurrency slot\n- Default: no limit (unlimited)\n- Set and query concurrency limit and current active count\n- Concurrency interacts with priority ordering\n\n#### Phase 9: Progress Tracking and Cancellation\n- Processing task reports progress as percentage (0-100) with optional message\n- Query task's current progress\n- Subscribe to progress updates for task, receive notifications\n- Subscriptions cancellable (unsubscribe)\n- Cancel pending or processing tasks\n- Cancelled pending tasks removed from queue\n- Cancelled processing tasks status updated\n- Cancelled tasks never retried (even if retries remaining)\n\n#### Phase 10: Recurring Tasks\n- Schedule associates cron expression with queue and task template\n- Support simple cron subset:\n  - `*/N * * * *` - every N minutes\n  - `0 * * * *` - every hour on the hour\n  - `0 0 * * *` - every day at midnight\n- Create, remove, and list active schedules\n- Manual \"tick\" or \"check\" mechanism evaluates schedules, enqueues due tasks (for testing)\n- Recurring tasks are regular tasks subject to all other queue rules\n- Removing schedule stops future occurrences\n\n#### Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline\n- Register middleware functions per queue\n- Task passes through all middleware in order before reaching handler\n- Each middleware receives task and \"next\" function\n- Calling \"next\" passes to next middleware (or handler)\n- Not calling \"next\" skips task processing\n- Middleware can modify task (metadata, transform payload)\n- Middleware error: task marked as failed\n- Register processing function/handler per queue (invoked after middleware)\n- Each queue has independent middleware stack\n\n#### Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown\n- Shutdown operation signals system to stop accepting new tasks\n- Adding new tasks after shutdown produces error\n- Shutdown waits for currently-processing tasks to finish (configurable timeout)\n- Tasks not completing within timeout: force-cancelled\n- Register callbacks to run during shutdown process\n- Shutdown produces summary: tasks completed, force-cancelled, time taken\n- Multiple shutdown calls safe, return same result\n- No processing tasks: shutdown completes immediately\n\n---\n\n### 4. Configuration Files\n\n#### package.json\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-task-queue\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Task queue marathon benchmark\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@types/node\": \"^25.2.3\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"@vitest/coverage-v8\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n#### tsconfig.json\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true,\n    \"forceConsistentCasingInFileNames\": true,\n    \"resolveJsonModule\": true,\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"declarationMap\": true,\n    \"sourceMap\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*\"],\n  \"exclude\": [\"node_modules\", \"dist\", \"tests\"]\n}\n```\n\n#### vitest.config.ts\n```typescript\nimport { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config';\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  test: {\n    globals: true,\n    testTimeout: 10000,\n  },\n});\n```\n\n#### .eslintrc.cjs\n```javascript\nmodule.exports = {\n  parser: '@typescript-eslint/parser',\n  plugins: ['@typescript-eslint'],\n  extends: ['eslint:recommended', 'plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended'],\n  parserOptions: {\n    ecmaVersion: 2022,\n    sourceType: 'module',\n  },\n  rules: {\n    '@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars': ['error', { argsIgnorePattern: '^_', varsIgnorePattern: '^_' }],\n  },\n  env: {\n    node: true,\n    es2022: true,\n  },\n};\n```\n\n#### .gitignore\n```\nnode_modules/\ndist/\n*.tsbuildinfo\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Source Code Status\n\n**Current State:** The `/workspace/src/` directory is empty except for a `.gitkeep` file. No source code has been implemented yet.\n\n---\n\n### Key Insights\n\n1. **Build Tools**: TypeScript 5.4 with strict mode enabled, ESLint for code quality, Vitest for testing\n2. **Module System**: ES modules (Node16)\n3. **Output Targets**: ES2022, declaration files with s