down**\n\n**Requirement:** \"A shutdown operation should signal the system to stop accepting new tasks.\"\n- **Status:** IMPLEMENTED ✓\n- **Details:** `isShuttingDown` flag is checked in `addTask()` (line 37) and `addSchedule()` (line 493)\n\n**Requirement:** \"After shutdown is initiated, attempting to add new tasks should produce an error.\"\n- **Status:** IMPLEMENTED ✓\n- **Details:** Lines 37-39 throw error\n\n**Requirement:** \"The shutdown should wait for all currently-processing tasks to finish, up to a configurable timeout.\"\n- **Status:** IMPLEMENTED ✓\n- **Details:** Lines 691-707 implement wait with timeout\n\n**Requirement:** \"If processing tasks do not complete within the timeout, they should be force-cancelled.\"\n- **Status:** IMPLEMENTED ✓\n- **Details:** Lines 713-717 force-cancel remaining processing tasks\n\n**Requirement:** \"Callbacks can be registered to run during the shutdown process.\"\n- **Status:** IMPLEMENTED ✓\n- **Details:** `onShutdown()` method exists\n\n**Requirement:** \"The shutdown should produce a summary indicating how many tasks completed, how many were force-cancelled, and how long the shutdown took.\"\n- **Status:** IMPLEMENTED ✓\n- **Details:** Lines 720-724 return `ShutdownResult`\n\n**Requirement:** \"Calling shutdown multiple times should be safe and return the same result.\"\n- **Status:** IMPLEMENTED ✓\n- **Details:** Lines 651-657 return cached `shutdownPromise`\n\n**Requirement:** \"If no tasks are processing, shutdown should complete immediately.\"\n- **Status:** IMPLEMENTED ✓\n- **Details:** Lines 683-689 return immediately if no processing tasks\n\nAll Phase 12 requirements appear properly implemented.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Issues Found\n\n### Critical Issues:\n1. **Phase 10 - Cron Expression Parsing:** The `shouldRunSchedule()` function only parses minute and hour fields. The `0 0 * * *` pattern (every day at midnight) cannot be correctly identified because the day-of-month field is never checked. **This will 